g.text: Payphone: "So nice of you to find the time to call me! It gets so lonely. Even the animals have died."
Payphone: "What a pity... I'm afraid I won't be coming to the funeral. I.... there... chrysanthemum..."

Payphone: "But who are you then? A salesman of some sort? Modern goods are rubbish. And I can't afford them anyhow. It's a shame what you did to our country..." The woman moans and the phone lines howl in unison with her.
You: "I'm not a salesman, I was just calling a random number and you somehow ran with it."
You: "I don't know who I am... But who are you?"
You: "Yes, I'm a salesman. What exactly did we do to your country?"
Payphone: Her voice is drowned in white noise. Sounds like waves washing a beach, growing in volume until the call suddenly disconnects.
Interfacing: 11 -- 17 -- 361 -- your fingers keep moving like a spider, every time the ring rotates back with a little ring of metal, like a bell tolling.
Payphone: "You shouldn't mess with people like this..." His voice is very calm. "You go have a nice day now."
Payphone: "Very funny, asshole. Why don't you grow up! Oh, and disco is dead!"
Payphone: "Harry, please..." A sad voice answers, dressed in distortion.
Electrochemistry: Underneath it she is naked and warm under a blanket.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You were making *prank calls*." Not a muscle moves in the lieutenant's face.
Esprit de Corps: This has lowered his opinion of you -- but only a little.
Payphone: "My *debt?* I don't fucking owe you, it's..." The young man realises something. "Who is... ah never mind, I don't have time for this..."
Suggestion: He does not seem to be overly thankful of your kindness as he hangs up.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant is too far away to hear your yelp. The sea wind blows...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's just go, I've had enough of this phone booth."
Empathy: The saddest sound in the world.
Volition: That's right. You *can*. Whatever you're doing here, you can just stop it and go on with your life.
Volition: You can't. Some strange force is keeping the headset glued to your hand, your ear listening to the ring in the speaker...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant shrugs apathetically, then walks a little distance away to concentrate on his notes. Looks like he'd rather not get into it again.
Payphone: "Oh god..." There's silence, it's heavy as tin. The white noise howls.
You: "I want to talk about me. Who am I? You sound like you know me."
Payphone: "What do you want to talk about? That we haven't talked about already..."
Volition: Right now. I'm gonna give you *one* chance.
Shivers: Run. To the church. Home. Anywhere but here. Anything but calling her again.
Perception (Hearing): In the distorted distance you hear someone turning next to her. Bedsprings rattle.
You: "It gets lonely even when you're with people."
You: "What kind of pets did you have?"
Payphone: "He's my sister's grandson. He used to visit me as a lad... Fine young man..."
Payphone: "This is because we are bred to be leaders. I can hear the common or mixed background from your voice."
Payphone: "I just so wanted it to be Pierre... Have a pleasant evening, prankster."
Payphone: "You're either a salesman or a statistician of some kind. I am not interested in cooperating."
Payphone: Someone with a masculine voice picks up:
You: "I don't know why I said that."
Payphone: "Oh no... is that you?" Her voice sounds like she's waking up now. Still plaintive, tired...
Payphone: "What are you, like five?" A woman's voice shouts something in the background and when Girard speaks again his voice is hushed...
Interfacing: 451 -- you have dialled god knows how many numbers. The headset has been waiting silently to relay a signal -- surely nothing can come of this, you think. But it does. A connection.
Volition: Now walk away. Forget about this. Walk away and do police work. *BURY* this in yourself and move on.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What the hell are you doing?" The lieutenant has been keeping a distance, but steps closer now.
Volition: What in the name of god did you just do?
Authority: Before it's too late, please.
Interfacing: Again you close your eyes -- and again your fingers move on the rotary dial. Ten metallic rings as the dial returns to zero after each number.
Interfacing: You close your eyes and feel your finger move on the rotary dial. You start with 005, as before...
Interfacing: What were you trying to achieve by closing your eyes? Did you want your muscle memory to take over and call somewhere? Where?
Half Light: Pitiful and terrifying. You feel your pulse rise with each ring...
Interfacing: You dialled 001. This is not the area code of Revachol. It is another destination -- on another isola. Some far-off nation state.
Encyclopedia: 005 is Revachol ZoC -- 001 is Graad, on the Graadian isola, where the telephone was invented. The next two digits you dial are the area code for the city of Mirova...
Pain Threshold: Fuck it, it doesn't hurt.
Kim Kitsuragi: "That's enough now, officer..." The lieutenant stands at a distance.
Payphone: A metal payphone under a yellow plastic dome. There's a bitter, caustic taste on the tip of your tongue as you look at the handset.
Drama: What *you* are is a *surprise*, get his wife on the phone...
Payphone: "Writing. I hate writing so much... But I have to get back to it."
Payphone: The man disappears with a sigh.
You: "My heart hurts. I'm gonna have a heart attack."
"My heart hurts. I'm gonna have another heart attack."
Payphone: "Oh no... please stop. Please let's just hang up..."
Payphone: You hear the tone -- the machine is operable.
Payphone: "You ruined it and you sold it to foreigners. You don't own anything if everything is for sale."
Payphone: It didn't give you *any* fun for that money. Nothing. Your hand is turning blue now... blood drips to the ground.
Payphone: It didn't give you *any* fun for that money. Your hand is turning blue now... blood drips to the ground.
You: "Get away from her, I'm a cop!"
Payphone: You can't make out a single word, just vague voices. One more, a child, has joined. Something breaks -- or falls over? Footsteps approaching!
Payphone: Something hits the phone with a loud crack of plastic and microphone hiss -- after that you are left with the disconnect tone.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What the hell are you doing?" The lieutenant has been keeping a distance, but steps closer now.
You: "You're right, Kim -- it went wrong. Horribly wrong. I shouldn't have done this..." (Hang up.)
You: "What? I'm just having a bit of fun, what's the big deal?"
You: "You seem to be in some sort of trouble. Maybe I can help you, I'm a police officer."
Payphone: The phone gets hanged up fast as lightning, all you hear is a little shuffle of nylon as the hand moves on the other end.
You: "I'm not drunk or high, I'm just... hurt... why does it hurt to talk to you?"
You: "Okay I'm drunk, what does it matter? I'm still *me*!"
You: "Harry? How do you know my name?"
You: "Harry? Who's Harry -- are you sleeping with him? I'm also Harry!"
You: "Harry? Who's Harry -- are you sleeping with him? Is *Harry* there?!"
You: "I'm gonna get even drunker." (Take a big sip.)
Pain Threshold: You just do. And you know it is going to hurt.
Horrific Necktie: Yeah, *bratan*. We've had all the fun there was to have here. And it wasn't much.
Payphone: It didn't give you *any* fun for that money.
Pain Threshold: Your hand is swelling up.
Payphone: "You're not an amnesiac, Harry... You're drunk."
Logic: You only have two, maybe three things left to say before the change runs out.
Payphone: "I don't understand what you're saying."
Encyclopedia: Twenty-two million people live in Mirova, the capital city of Graad. It is the capital of the world after Revachol was destroyed.
Payphone: End of tone. Someone picks up.
Payphone: "Pierre? Is that you, Pierre?" The voice is female and sounds about a hundred years old.
You: Put 10 cents in and dial a random number: 005-24-03-155.
You: "You're naked, aren't you?" (Beat the handset against the phone.)
Payphone: You can't hear her reply.
Payphone: "Wh-who is this?" The man does not understand.
You: "I'm sorry it was a stupid joke, I shouldn't have called, it's stupid -- I'm so sorry."
You: "It's Harry, put her on, I don't like waiting."
You: "Doesn't matter, put her on, I don't like waiting."
You: "It's Pierre, now put her on. I don't like waiting."
Payphone: More shouting. You're pretty sure you hear a man saying *fuck* several times. Then the crackle in the phone line gets violently loud, like the surf breaking.
Physical Instrument: You hear a faint *thuck*. You could swear you're hearing furniture falling over.
Interfacing: 41 -- 44 -- 47 -- the rotary dial feels cold from the sea air.
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""Big deal?!" Not a muscle moves in..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Big deal?!" Not a muscle moves in the lieutenant's face.
Payphone: Your hand isn't moving. The headset hisses in your ear with *evil* sadness.
Payphone: She does not answer anymore.
You: "None of it matters -- not anymore."
You: "Can you help me solve it? I need to solve it. They won't take me back if I don't."
You: "It doesn't matter. This case doesn't matter."
Payphone: "Are you sure you're Pierre? Your voice, it's different... I... there... chrysanthemum..."
Payphone: You dial the number again -- as you've done many times. You remember it well now: 001 -- 41 -- 44 -- 47 -- 11 -- 17 -- 361 -- 451 -- 67 -- 451 -- 451.
Empathy: It looks like she does not want to pick it up, Harry. Stop scaring her.
You: "I am the last faithful kingsman. I will free the city of Revachol. I will turn back the sea. I will reverse time." (Proceed.)
Payphone: "You're not a kingsman, Harry... You're drunk."
Payphone: In the middle of it -- a familiar ring. Small. Distorted.
Payphone: And calling -- for two minutes now. You're out of luck. No one's home there either. But the payphone still has your ten cents in there...
Payphone: You pick up the handset. There's a tone -- the machine is operable.
Payphone: Then the ocean breaks. Out of the depths, a woman's voice emerges. Small. The dearest thing you've ever heard.
Payphone: Static sings inside the phone glued to your ear. Ancient, sticky...
Payphone: She does not answer. All you hear is hiss.
Inland Empire: Dora. The name feels like a *gift*. A gift that was meant for you -- to make it possible to live.
Volition: Don't react. Whatever you do, don't react to that last thing.
Payphone: "To hell with the police! To hell with you..."
Payphone: A sigh. She heard you, but she does not hang up. And neither do you. You can't.
Jump to: [Payphone: "The headset lands in the cradle wit..."]
Payphone: The headset lands in the cradle with a clank.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You're right, you shouldn't have."
You: "We could all be a bit kinder to each other, don't you think? Consider your debt paid, my friend."
Endurance: The handset starts slipping from your sweaty palm... your breathing is heavy.
Inland Empire: It's *really* time to stop this now.
Interfacing: 41 -- 44 -- 47 -- it's too late now, the movement is almost mechanical.
You: "You want my MONEY?!" (Punch the phone.)
You: "Is there anything I can do to help you? I'm with the police."
Volition: You need to stop, Harry. You'll die.
Payphone: "You're not a revolutionary, Harry... You're drunk."
You: "A creature is a creature. I wish I was the wind."
Payphone: "Oh no, not this... what time is it?"
You: "Your voice makes me want to turn into dust."
You: "I am an ultra-high-net-worth individual. I understand how reality works. I have *seen* into it. My mind is clear." (Proceed.)
Payphone: "You're not a high-net-worth individual, Harry... You're drunk."
Payphone: "Dora." She's still confused. "Who is this? The connection is bad..."
Payphone: "You're not ominous, Harry... You're drunk."
You: Long windows... how do I know that?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Are we about *done* with this now?" The lieutenant has taken a few steps back.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Khm..." A single *khm* lets you know the lieutenant is ready to move now.
Inland Empire: Who cares. Run. Go. Don't think about this. Do police work, it's all there is.
Drama: No, what *you* are is a *surprise*, get his wife on the phone...
Payphone: "I'm tired..." A man answers, fast this time. His voice is hoarse from cigarettes. You hear typing in the background.
Perception (Hearing): Sounds like he hasn't talked to anyone in quite a while.
Payphone: "If I could go just one month without writing. No, two months... I could regenerate my brain. Fucking liberalism..."
Inland Empire: He doesn't have a home. His home is under a boat.
You: "The Academy? That sounds better than my job. I'm happy."
You: "My job is sad and terrible. It has dead bodies in it."
You: I'm making a funny prank call.
Volition: Fun? You need to stop. Harry. You're killing yourself.
Physical Instrument: Push the headset in the cradle with all the strength you have!
You: Smash the headset into the cradle.
You: No. I can't. I need the pain.
Payphone: The cord dangles in the wind like a sickening worm.
Payphone: And calling -- for who knows how long. But no one answers. You need to insert more money to call again.
Inland Empire: You get a sinking feeling. It makes you look if Lieutenant Kitsuragi overheard you. To your relief, he did not.
Conceptualization: Hello, Girard. Technically speaking, you're electricity.
Payphone: "Mhm," she hums, her voice warm from sleep.
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""You're right, you shouldn't have.""]
Interfacing: Strange. This is not how you started before.
You: Wait -- what did I just do?

Payphone: An ultra-long-distance call. Your ear fills with a crackle, the wash of a strange ocean full of white noise. A little bird starts ringing in there, not like the local calling tone before. No, a small ring in a cage of distortion, far away, a distant network of phones...
Payphone: There's a moment of silence before the voice speaks again, more calmly: "You got the wrong number, don't call here again."
Payphone: Time keeps passing. In the distance, seagulls squawk -- no one is home at this number. But the coin... it's still in there... you find yourself thinking:
You: "I don't know who I am. I am an amnesiac." (Proceed.)
You: "I might be? What's Pierre like?"
Payphone: "Because it's me... Look, I don't understand what you're saying or why you're calling me. You seem drunk."
You: I don't know... I don't understand what's happening.
Payphone: She sighs. "Look, I don't understand what you're saying, or why you're calling me. You seem drunk."
Payphone: "Do you have any news about Pierre?"
Interfacing: Yes. 451 -- 67 -- 451 -- you are going deeper now, into some unknown place. Far away from this island of matter and its telecommunication networks....
Perception (Hearing): No answer. You're not sure but you think you hear a *man's* voice in the background. It's covered in pain and white noise...
You: Put 10 cents in and dial a random number: 005-99-77-313.
You: "Hey, Girard, get your wife for me, will you?"
You: "Girard... what a douche name... Change it -- change your name!"
Payphone: The sounds are muffled. You can make out two people: a man and a woman called *Bian*. They are talking to each other in agitated voices. There's a shuffle of feet, children maybe?
Perception (Hearing): Amid the howling in the wire you make out a woman's voice with a thick Samaran accent: "Girard... Girard, this is a joke. Someone is making a joke..."
You: Put 10 cents in and dial the long phone number again.
Payphone: You dial the number again -- twenty six pulls of the rotary dial. The machine eats the coin and a terrifying ocean of distance rustles in your ear...
You: No. Let it call. I *must*.
Jump to: [Payphone: "No response, only a sigh. The conne..."]
Payphone: No response, only a sigh. The connection crackles, like burning paper.
You: "I am the law. I'm a detective. I'm doing a case. There's a hanged man."
Payphone: "Please. I am going to hang up now, okay?"
You: "Is Alec Tricity there? I need to speak with Alec Tricity, please."
You: "I'm the guy who's fucking your wife, Girard. Now put her on before I lose my patience."
Payphone: "Just tell me what's going on here!" Now you hear fear too. The voice gets further away from the microphone, then yells: "Bian, come here!"
Payphone: "Stop calling me, man!" Someone picks up. The voice on the other end is slightly hysterical.
Payphone: There's still some unused change in there -- the machine waits for a number to be dialled.
Pain Threshold: Punch it again, the pain is good.
Payphone: "I'll get you your money, alright? I just need 'til tonight. Let me work."
Payphone: "Do you know what time it is? It's so late here..." Sounds like she's looking for a clock on the night stand.
Payphone: "It's four o'clock, Harry! I need to wake up in two hours."
You: "Where are you? You sound like you're in another world."
You: "Where are you going in two hours?"
Volition: You need to stop. Harry. You're killing yourself.
Pain Threshold: No. We're not gonna do this. Your hand is *not* going to cramp up, not now.
You: "I'm no one, I'm sorry, I shouldn't have done this..."
Pain Threshold: That's it. You're caught in a trap. It'll take quite a while for the shit-circus to end now.
You: "I was just having a bit of fun, what's the big deal?"
Volition: What are you doing to yourself right now?
Payphone: Pause. There is silence on the other end.
Payphone: "You won't get me and you won't get my money!"
You: Dial a random number -- with your eyes closed.
You: Put 10 cents in and dial a random number: 005-51-17-912.
You: Put 10 cents in and dial a random number: 005-11-11-313.
You: Put 10 cents in and dial the long phone number one more time.
You: "You want more money now, huh?! YOU WANT FUCKING MONEY?!!!?" (Punch the phone again.)
Payphone: "No, but I got a feeling Al Kickurass is gonna make an appearance if you ever call this number again. Have a good one, asshole!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer -- that's enough. Let's return to work..."
Payphone: The headset lands in the cradle with a clank. There it sits -- still warm from your hand. You have no idea what just happened.
Payphone: "Sure you do. No one has anything nowadays."
Payphone: A metal payphone under a yellow plastic dome. You could use it to call someone, unless you're out of change...
You: "'Harry please?!' -- I am going to *end* this call, dammit."
Payphone: "Don't worry about it, buddy -- happens to all of us. You have a nice day now!"
You: "Wait Girard! Let's just keep talking, buddy!"
Encyclopedia: The area code for Revachol Zone of Control.
Payphone: Followed by seven digits at random. The last one makes the silence turn into a ring. It's calling...
Half Light: Both pitiful and terrifying. You feel your pulse rising with each ring...
Payphone: "No, I want to go to sleep..."
Payphone: Disconnect tone -- the machine ran out of money.
Inland Empire: This feels wrong. Should you be doing this?
Payphone: "Who the fuck do you think you are talking to me like that?" The voice on the phone is suddenly very agitated.
You: "Stop it! I was just kidding, I'm not sleeping with your wife!"
You: "I'm not going to stop. I'm going to keep fucking your wife, Girard."
Interfacing: You close your eyes and put your index finger on the rotary dial, then pull down on the number, then move one up and repeat the motion, twice...
Payphone: The cold metal is hard and hurts your knuckles. You look at them turning purple.
Endurance: This is bad, you feel your right hand on the handset cramping up with pain...
Electrochemistry: Takes your mind away from that voice, for one second at least...
Pain Threshold: Ringing by the bedside of a dark but capacious apartment with long windows... you know this to be true.
Logic: Seems like it did not have time to swallow the coin. This sometimes happens.
Interfacing: Lucky you. The call went too fast for the payphone to register. You can still make a new one without paying.
Inland Empire: He doesn't have a home. Not anymore.
You: "There was someone there before. I heard someone. Who's there with you?"
Perception (Hearing): It doesn't matter if you react or not. You still think you hear a *man's* voice in the background. It's covered in pain and white noise...
You: "I need to know who you are. WHO ARE YOU?!"
You: "I'm a revolutionary servant of humanity. I will free mankind and abolish the classes. I will raise the dead." (Proceed.)
Payphone: "What?" It takes a second for her to realize what you said.
You: "Yes, but a slight change of plans -- I want this delivered to the Whirling-in-Rags in Martinaise."
Payphone: "Tethys, I uh..." The young man realises something. "Hey, you're not Tethys! Screw you and don't ever call here again, you're fucking with some *serious* people!"
Payphone: "No-no..." She's waking up now. "It's *you*, isn't it? It's you..."
Payphone: The cold metal is hard and your knuckles bleed a little...
Payphone: You do not hear the customary disconnect tone, just silence in the handset -- the machine is still waiting for you to dial a number.
You: "I want to live -- with you..."
"I want to live -- with you..." (Take a sip from the bottle -- your throat is parched all of a sudden.)
You: "You're right, Kim -- this went wrong, I shouldn't have done this..."
You: "I don't understand what I did wrong."
Reaction Speed: Say you're not Pierre... that seems like a better idea. (You don't know why.)
Payphone: Silence. The connection falters. You hear her last words repeated back to you in an echo:
Payphone: The cold metal is hard and your knuckles bleed.
You: "I can't *tell* you who I am. I have a secret plan to win mankind three thousand years of peace on this planet. I have to be ominously vague..." (Proceed.)
Conceptualization: This is too much... You need to recede...
